							<span class="type">string</span>
							<code class="name">$rule</code>
															<span class="parameter">
									<p>If $name is a string, this should be a string regular expression, or a
closure that returns a boolean indicating success. Should be left blank if
<code>$name</code> is an array.</p>
								</span>
													</li>
											<li>
							<span class="type">array</span>
							<code class="name">$options</code>
															<span class="parameter">
									<p>The default options for validating this rule. An option which applies
to all regular expression rules is <code>'contains'</code> which, if set to true, allows
validated values to simply <em>contain</em> a match to a rule, rather than exactly
matching it in whole.</p>
								</span>
